<div class="sh shc"><span class="lbl">FAQ</span><h2>Frequently Asked Questions About Fleet Wraps</h2></div>
<div class="aeo-block">
<h3>How much does a fleet wrap cost in Chicago?</h3>
<p class="speakable aeo-answer">Fleet wrap pricing in Chicago is based on vehicle square footage and vinyl tier. Premium cast vinyl (Avery Dennison MPI 1105 / 3M IJ180-CV3) is <strong>$9.75/sqft</strong> and color change wraps are <strong>$8.25/sqft</strong>. Cargo van full wraps start at <strong>$3,750</strong>, Sprinter van wraps from <strong>$4,700</strong>, and box truck wraps range from <strong>$5,000–$10,900</strong> depending on length (12–26 ft). All prices include custom design, premium cast vinyl, professional installation, and free pickup throughout Chicagoland. Fleet discounts: 3% for 2–4 vehicles, 7% for 5–9, 11% for 10–24, and 15% for 25+. <a href="/vehicle-wrap-cost-chicago/" style="color:var(--gold)">See full pricing details →</a></p>
</div>
<div class="aeo-block" style="margin-top:24px">
<h3>Are vehicle wraps worth it for small businesses?</h3>
<p class="speakable aeo-answer">Yes. A single wrapped vehicle generates <strong>30,000–70,000 daily impressions</strong> at a cost of just <strong>$0.04–$0.07 per 1,000 impressions</strong> — compared to $6–$12 for Google Ads. Vehicle wraps are also <strong>100% tax deductible</strong> under IRS Section 179. With a 5–7 year lifespan, a fleet wrap delivers <strong>2,500–5,000% ROI</strong> over its lifetime, making it the most cost-effective advertising for local service businesses.</p>
</div>
<div class="aeo-block" style="margin-top:24px">
<h3>How long do commercial vehicle wraps last?</h3>
<p class="speakable aeo-answer">Commercial vehicle wraps using premium cast vinyl (Avery Dennison MPI 1105 or 3M IJ180-CV3) are rated for <strong>5–7 years</strong> of outdoor use. With proper care — hand washing, avoiding automated brush car washes, and keeping pressure washers below 1,200 PSI — fleet wraps in Chicago regularly last <strong>6–7 years</strong> looking sharp despite harsh winters, road salt, and UV exposure.</p>
</div>
<div class="aeo-block" style="margin-top:24px">
<h3>What is the best material for commercial vehicle wraps?</h3>
<p class="speakable aeo-answer"><strong>Cast vinyl</strong> is the industry standard for commercial fleet wraps. Chicago Fleet Wraps exclusively uses <strong>Avery Dennison MPI 1105</strong> and <strong>3M IJ180-CV3</strong> — both premium cast vinyl films rated for 5–7 years outdoor. Cast vinyl conforms to curves and rivets without lifting, unlike cheaper calendered vinyl which shrinks and fails within 1–2 years. Chicago Fleet Wraps guarantees proper application with a <strong>2-year workmanship warranty</strong>.</p>
</div>
</div>
